    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider a Boolean gate (D) where the output Y is related to the inputs A and b as, Y = A + $$\\overline B $$, where + denotes logical OR operation. The Boolean inputs '0' and '1' are also available separately. Using instances of only D gates and inputs '0' and '1', ___________ (select the correct options).</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "NAND logic can be implemented"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "OR logic cannot be implemented"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "NOR logic can be implemented"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "AND logic cannot be implemented"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A",
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>F(A, B) = A + $$\\overline B $$</p>\n<p>As 0 and 1 are available.</p>\n<p>F(0, B) = A + $$\\overline B $$ = 0 + $$\\overline B $$</p>\n<p>= $$\\overline B $$ (NOT)</p>\n<p>F(A + $$\\overline B $$) = A + $$\\overline{\\overline B} $$ = A + B</p>\n<p>F(A + $$\\overline B$$) = A + B (OR)</p>\n<p>With the combination of OR and NOT, NOR gate can be implemented.</p>\n<p>Since NOR gate is universal logic gate, so all the functions can be implemented.</p>\n<p>So, correct option is (a, c).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "content": "The logic gates shown in the digital circuit below use strong pull-down nMOS transistors for\nLOW logic level at the outputs. When the pull-downs are off, high-value resistors set the\noutput logic levels to HIGH (i.e. the pull-ups are weak). Note that some nodes are\nintentionally shorted to implement “wired logic”. Such shorted nodes will be HIGH only if\nthe outputs of all the gates whose outputs are shorted are HIGH.\n<br><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf7629jjz2hutly/4ae4fc4a-01eb-45a6-a9a0-73a606cc43d4/02947060-b9c1-11e9-8dd7-afa307a7b101/file-jf7629jjz2hutlz-320w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf7629jjz2hutly/4ae4fc4a-01eb-45a6-a9a0-73a606cc43d4/02947060-b9c1-11e9-8dd7-afa307a7b101/file-jf7629jjz2hutlz-500w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2018 Digital Circuits - Logic Gates Question 4 English\"></picture>\n<br><br>The number of distinct values of X<sub>3</sub>X<sub>2</sub>X<sub>1</sub>X<sub>0</sub> (out of the 16 possible values) that give\n𝑌 = 1 is _______.",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "8 to 8",
    "explanation": "<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf7629jjz2i4wek/66dfbde9-b35a-44ef-99ee-2dd6fe6709d0/1ad484c0-b9c2-11e9-8dd7-afa307a7b101/file-jf7629jjz2i4wel-320w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jf7629jjz2i4wek/66dfbde9-b35a-44ef-99ee-2dd6fe6709d0/1ad484c0-b9c2-11e9-8dd7-afa307a7b101/file-jf7629jjz2i4wel-500w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2018 Digital Circuits - Logic Gates Question 4 English Explanation\"></picture>\n<br><br>From figure, M = $$\\left( {{X_1} \\oplus {X_2}} \\right){\\overline X _3}$$\n<br><br>N = $$\\left( {A.{X_0}} \\right){\\overline X _0}$$\n<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; = 0 [ as $${X_0}{\\overline X _0}$$ = 0 ]\n<br><br>Y = (N + X<sub>3</sub>) = X<sub>3</sub>\n<br><br>The number of distinct values possible with X<sub>3</sub>X<sub>2</sub>X<sub>1</sub>X<sub>0</sub> = 16. And out of 16 combinations <b>8</b> such combination present when X<sub>3</sub> = 1 and gives output Y = 1.",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2018,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2018",
    "difficulty": null
  },
