    "content": "All the logic gates shown in the figure have a propagation delay of 20 ns. Let A = C = 0 and B = 1\nuntil time t = 0. At t = 0, all the inputs flip (i.e., A = C = 1 and B = 0) and remain in that state. For\nt &gt; 0, output Z = 1 for a duration (in ns) of ______________. \n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kwp89fex/1987c5da-28bb-471d-8501-63e459108ad7/a7e6aaa0-5394-11ec-bfd6-3905384ffb4d/file-1kwp89fey.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kwp89fex/1987c5da-28bb-471d-8501-63e459108ad7/a7e6aaa0-5394-11ec-bfd6-3905384ffb4d/file-1kwp89fey.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2015 Set 1 Digital Circuits - Logic Gates Question 10 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "40",
